{"comments":"Pipage Rounding Algorithm.\n\n## Theoretical Foundation\n\nPipage rounding converts fractional solutions to integral solutions while:\n1. Maintaining feasibility (output is always matroid-independent)\n2. Preserving marginals: E[1_e ∈ S] = x_e for all elements e\n3. Never decreasing expected value: E[f(S)] ≥ F(x)\n\nThe key insight: for submodular functions, the multilinear extension F\nis concave along \"pipage\" directions (transfer probability between elements).\n\n## Pipage Direction\n\nA pipage step between elements i and j with transfer ε:\n  x'_i = x_i + ε\n  x'_j = x_j - ε\n\nThe multilinear extension F is piecewise linear along this direction.\nWe move to a \"breakpoint\" where either x'_i ∈ {0,1} or x'_j ∈ {0,1}.\n\n## References\n\n- Ageev, Sviridenko. \"Pipage Rounding: A New Method of Constructing\n  Algorithms with Proven Performance Guarantee\" J. Comb. Opt. 2004\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Hydrogen.Optimize.Submodular.Types (element types)\n- Hydrogen.Optimize.Submodular.Continuous (fractional solutions)\n- Hydrogen.Optimize.Submodular.Rounding.Util (utility functions)\n- Hydrogen.Optimize.Submodular.Rounding.Pairing (element pairing)\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Record"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["solution",{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Optimize","Submodular","Continuous","FractionalSolution"],"FractionalSolution"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":"v","tag":"TypeVar"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["integral",{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Optimize","Submodular","Types","GroundSet"],"ElementSet"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":"v","tag":"TypeVar"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["excluded",{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Optimize","Submodular","Types","GroundSet"],"ElementSet"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":"v","tag":"TypeVar"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["steps",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["seed",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"tag":"REmpty"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[109,4],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Optimize/Submodular/Rounding/Pipage.purs","start":[103,23]},"title":"PipageState"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Optimize","Submodular","Rounding","Pipage"],"PipageState"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":"v","tag":"TypeVar"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[115,55],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Optimize/Submodular/Rounding/Pipage.purs","start":[111,1]},"title":"showPipageState"}],"comments":"State for pipage rounding algorithm.\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"newtype","declType":"data","roles":["Nominal"],"typeArguments":[["v",null]]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[109,4],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Optimize/Submodular/Rounding/Pipage.purs","start":[103,1]},"title":"PipageState"},{"children":[],"comments":"Create initial pipage state.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":{"identifier":"v","kind":null,"skolem":null,"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Optimize","Submodular","Continuous","FractionalSolution"],"Fr